<subSubSection id="02C66578FFFBFFBAFC959A5D6A7E7A6C" pageId="22" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFBFFBAFC959A5D6AC77B31" blockId="22.[830,1437,1561,1805]" pageId="22" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFBFFBAFC959A5D6ABD7B50" bold="true" box="[831,944,1561,1585]" pageId="22" pageNumber="36">Remarks:</emphasis>
It has a wide, coiled chambers and high rugosity test.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFBFFBAFC959A1C6A7E7A6C" blockId="22.[830,1437,1561,1805]" pageId="22" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFBFFBAFC959A1C6D7C7B11" bold="true" box="[831,1137,1624,1648]" pageId="22" pageNumber="36">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It was originally described from the Late Cretaceous of the Paris Basin by D’ORBIGNY (1840). It is recorded in the Maastrichtian by SAID &amp; KENAWY (1956) and LUGER (1985). It is found in the Maastrichtian and Paleocene of the Esh El Mallaha area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
